Title: Benno Moiseiwitsch plays Tchaikovsky Piano Concerto No.2 Op.44
Description:
Benno Moiseiwitsch (1890 - 1963), was a Ukrainian-born British pianist. He was particularly known for his interpretations of the late Romantic repertoire, especially the works of Sergei Rachmaninoff. Moiseiwitsch was noted for his elegance, poetry, lyrical phrasing, brilliance, rhythmic freedom, and relaxed virtuosity.

Title: Mikhail Pletnev plays Tchaikovsky Piano Concerto no. 2, op. 44 - live 1979
Description:
A sensational recording of Mikhail Pletnev playing Tchaikovsky's Piano Concerto no. 2, op. 44, with the Bulgarian Radio SO under Vassil Stefanov, live on 18 January 1979. The engineer messed up the first 90 seconds with the piano in the right channel only, which I've tried to correct. The rest of the recording is fine. The photo shows Pletnev with his teacher Evgeny Timakin. Timing below:

Title: Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky - Piano Concerto No. 2 in G major, Op. 44
Description: Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky's Piano Concerto No. 2 in G major, Op. 44, was written in 1879–1880. A Russian composer of the Romantic period. He was the first Russian composer whose music would make a lasting impression internationally.

Title: Tchaikovsky: Piano Concerto No. 2 with Bruce Liu
Description:
Bruce Liu, winner of the 2021 International Chopin Piano Competition, joins the Philharmonia Orchestra and Principal Conductor Santtu-Matias Rouvali in Tchaikovsky’s Piano Concerto No. 2. Bruce Liu made his UK debut in this performance, recorded live at the Royal Festival Hall in London on 10 March 2022.

Discover the rest of our videos about the piano here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLqR22EoucCyfc2x7UXWmGtbM2a7vg7fWE
